-sn → Skip port scanning; consider all hosts as alive
-Pn → Skip host discovery; scan directly for open ports
-p- → Scan all ports (0–65535)
-p 20,21,22 → Scan / exclude specific ports
-p 20-30 → Scan a specific port range
-n → Disable DNS resolution
-v → Enable verbose mode
--top-ports 100 → Scan the top 100 most common ports
--reason → Display the reason why a port is in a particular state
--open → Show only open ports in scan results

Service, OS & Advanced Scanning :
-sV → Enable service version detection
-O → Enable OS detection
-A → Enable aggressive scan {OS detection ,Service version detection ,It Run's Default NSE scripts}

Fast & Timing Options :
-F → Scan most common ports (100)

-T0 to -T5 → Control scan speed
T0 = Paranoid
T1 = Sneaky
T2 = Polite
T3 = Normal
T4 = Aggressive (recommended)
T5 = Insane

Output Options :
-oA → Output scan results in all formats
-oX → Output scan results in XML format
-oN → Output scan results in normal (human-readable) format

Scripting Engine : 
#-sC → Run Nmap default scripts against the target system

#nmap –script-help scriptname
•	Display detailed information about a specific nse script.

#nmap –script-update 
 Download the new nse scripts
 Update existing scripts to new version

#--script scriptname: Runs a specific Nmap NSE script to detect vulnerabilities, enumerate services, or gather detailed information from the target.

NOTE: cd /usr/share/nmap/scripts = where nmap .nse scripts file are stored 
